  "texts": [
    "The ECoG recordings provide a measure of the neural activity patterns for each word in the IFG.",
    "These activity patterns correspond to a local brain embedding for each word, where the activity of each electrode serves as a feature (i.e., dimension) in the IFG embedding space (Fig. 1D, left).",
    "Across all participants, we extracted an 81-dimensional brain embedding vector for each word in the story.",
    "The brain embeddings were sampled across all electrodes in IFG and identified anatomically during surgery without imposing any additional selection criteria.",
    "To assess the selectivity of the results, we also sampled activity from two anatomically adjacent brain regions containing a similar density of electrodes but not thought to be directly involved in language comprehension: the precentral gyrus and the postcentral gyrus."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}